Datos perdidos¶

Se toman las columan y se imputan a traves de

    • sueldo_smdlv has 111082 (60.1%) missing values Missing
    • otros_ingresos_smdlv has 179418 (97.1%) missing values
  • Categoricas
    • genero has 97541 (52.8%) missing values Missing
    • estado_civil has 102421 (55.4%) missing values Missing
    • municipio_expedicion has 93581 (50.6%) missing values Missing

from sklearn.impute import SimpleImputer

fields_imputer = {'edad': 'mean', 'sueldo_smdlv': 'mean', 'otros_ingresos_smdlv': 'mean', 'genero': 'most_frequent',
                  'estado_civil': 'most_frequent', 'municipio_expedicion': 'most_frequent', 'tiene_casa_propia': 'most_frequent'}
for key in fields_imputer:
    print('-'*50)
    imputer = SimpleImputer(missing_values=np.NaN, strategy=fields_imputer[key])
    print('\t{} with nan: {}'.format(key, X[key].isna().sum()))
    X[key] = imputer.fit_transform(X[key].values.reshape(-1,1), y.values.reshape(-1,1))[:,0]
    print('\t{} with out nan: {}'.format(key, X[key].isna().sum()))
    print(X[key].values[:10])
